<strong>LOOKING FORWARD</strong>
            <div class="fishing-line-separator"></div>

                <p>Through the Native Fish Strategy for the Murray-Darling Basin a concerted
effort is now being undertaken to bring back native fish populations. The
long-term goal is to see the native fish populations back to 60 per cent of
their estimated pre-European settlement levels—and to do this over a
fifty year period, or sooner. </p>


